     Photo of Victory Arch in Newport News

     Since World War I, thousands of the nation's soldiers have returned
   home amidst citizens' cheers as they passed beneath the Victory Arch in
   Newport News, Virginia. An eternal flame remembering their service and
   sacrifice burns in front of the arch.

